                <div class="border-redious p-3">
                    <p>
                        Digital Healthcare Solutions (DH), a social business committed to ensuring ‘Health For All’, partnered with USAID’s MaMoni Maternal and Newborn Care Strengthening Project: Emergency Response to COVID-19 Pandemic implemented by Save the Children in association with factories under BGMEA and BEPZA to serve 150,000 marginalized people of Bangladesh, including the RMG workers and slum dwellers of Dhaka, Gazipur, Narayanganj and Narsingdi. From 1st February till 30th June, the project provided free Shurokkhito package which included 24/7 doctor consultations via 08 000 111 000 (toll-free), specialist doctors of Gyneacology, Paediatrics, Dermatology, and Psychology, up to Tk. 20,000 Health Cashback covering Maternity and COVID-19 costs as well. Beneficiaries were able to avail Doctor Video Call through the Digital Hospital app.
                        Digital Doctor Booths were also set up at 7 large factories to make Doctor Video Call more accessible even to those who do not have smartphones. 41 day-long Health Camps with MBBS doctors were carried out at the RMG factories and slums, allowing people to receive primary care face to face from the doctors. Over 10,000 consultations via Doctor Call, 650+ consultations with Specialist Doctors and Tk. 217,000+ has already been paid out as Health Cashback.

                    </p>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
